message:
Now I have a full picture of the codebase. It's a single `index.html` file with inline CSS and JS. Here's my execution plan:

```json
{
  "summary": "Add a 'Clear completed' button that removes all completed tasks at once, with an undo toast for accidental deletion prevention",
  "subtasks": [
    {
      "title": "Add 'Clear completed' button to HTML and CSS",
      "description": "Add a 'Clear completed' button element below the filters row in the HTML. Style it as a small danger-style button that is hidden by default (display:none) and only shown when completed tasks exist. Add a `.clear-completed-btn` CSS rule and a `.toast` CSS rule for the undo notification that will appear bottom-center."
    },
    {
      "title": "Implement clearCompleted() and wire button visibility into render()",
      "description": "Add a `clearCompleted()` function that removes all tasks where `completed === true` from the `tasks` array, calls `saveTasks()`, then calls `render()`. Wire the button's click event to this function. Inside `render()`, show or hide the 'Clear completed' button based on whether `tasks.some(t => t.completed)` is true."
    },
    {
      "title": "Implement undo toast with auto-dismiss",
      "description": "Before clearing, snapshot the current tasks array. After clearing, show a fixed toast element (e.g. 'Completed tasks cleared. Undo') with an Undo button. Clicking Undo restores the snapshot, saves, and re-renders. The toast auto-dismisses after 4 seconds using setTimeout. Clear any pending timeout if Undo is clicked or a new clear is triggered."
    }
  ]
}
```
